Name: TypeOfVersionNumber
Description: This is the name of the versioning scheme as defined by the user's system, in cases where the user's system employs more than one versioning scheme.

Name: VersionResponsibility
Description: Person or organization within the MaintenanceAgency responsible for the version change. If it is important to retain the affiliation between and individual responsible for the version and his/her agency, it may be included in this notation. This is primarily intended for internal use.

Name: VersionResponsibilityReference
Description: Reference person or organization within the MaintenanceAgency responsible for the version change, as described in an OrganizationScheme. If it is important to retain the affiliation between and individual responsible for the version and his/her agency, a Relation should be created between the individual referenced here and his/her organization. This is primarily intended for internal use.

Name: VersionRationale
Description: Textual description of the rationale/purpose for a version change.

Name: VersionNumber
Description: The version number of the data file identified by this physical instance.

Name: VersionDate
Description: Date of version using the union set BaseDateType. Duration should not be used in this field, even though allowed by the ISO format enforced by the parser.
